
		DEMOS

	$Id$

	This file summarizes the various GEOS 2.0 demo versions and
	how to run them.

To install all demos
--------------------
Type:
	c:
	cd \
	n:\makedemo

This makes a directory for each product:
	c:\bbdemo.net
	c:\ensdemo.net
	c:\zoomdemo.net
	c:\bbdemo.ec
	c:\ensdemo.ec
	c:\zoomdemo.ec

These directories are copied from:
	n:\local\bb
	n:\local\ens
	n:\local\zoom
	n:\local\bbec
	n:\local\ensec
	n:\local\zoomec
	n:\local\redwood

and copies two batch files for each product, one to use the latest
version and one to use the last saved stable version:
	bb20.bat
	bb20sv.bat
	bb20ec.bat
	ens20.bat
	ens20sv.bat
	ens20ec.bat
	zoom20.bat
	zoom20sv.bat
	zoom20ec.bat
	redwdemo.bat


Batch files
-----------
The batch files look like:
	cd \ensdemo.net
	geos
or for the "sv" versions:
	cd \ensdemo.net
	n:\ensdemo.sv\loader /psaved
or for the "ec" versions:
	cd \ensdemo.ec
	n:\ensdemo.ec\loaderec

The geos.bat file in each directory looks like:
	n:\ensdemo\loader
or for the "sv" versions:
	n:\ensdemo.sv\loader /psaved
or for the "ec" versions:
	n:\ensdemo.ec\loaderec

The "/psaved" parameter causes the loader to look in the "inisaved"
category instead of the "ini" category.


.ini files
----------
The local geos.ini file starts with:
	ini = n:\ensdemo\net.ini
	inisaved = n:\ensdemo.sav\net.ini
and contains local settings.

The global .ini file contains:
	[paths]
	top = n:\ensdemo [.sv] [.ec]
	[ui]
	haveEnvironmentApp = true
	[uiFeatures]
	defaultLauncher = EC Welcome
	[uiFeatures - intro]
	...
	[uiFeatures - beginner]
	...
	[uiFeatures - advanced]
	...


Baseball
--------
This is a demonstration of the Baseball product.

Downloaded to:
    Current:
	DOS: GOBEARS/NEVADA:GEOS20\BBDEMO
	UNIX: /n/nevada/geos20/bbdemo
    Saved:
	DOS: GOBEARS/NEVADA:GEOS20\BBDEMO.SAV
	UNIX: /n/nevada/geos20/bbdemo.sav
    EC:
	DOS: GOBEARS/NEVADA:GEOS20\BBDEMO.EC
	UNIX: /n/nevada/geos20/bbdemo.ec

To run:
	bb20
	bb20sv
	bb20ec


